POD:
====

    * Basic execution unit in Kubernetes
    * Pods represents processes running on your cluster
    * Single instance of your application
    * Single Container per POD
    * Each POD has it own unique IP
    * Containers inside the POD communicate via the POD IP in a Localhost connection


    How to deploy PODS:
    ===================

        - Deploys a docker Container by creating a POD


        kubectl run nginx --image nginx
        kubectl get pods (ContainerCreating => Running)
        kubectl describe pods
        kubectl get pods -o wide


